Open Sans Light Regular (OpenSans-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Open Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Open Sans Light'.

Open Sans Light Italic (OpenSans-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Open Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Open Sans Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Open Sans Italic (OpenSans-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'OpenSans-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Open Sans Italic (OpenSans-Italic.ttf)

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'OpenSans-Italic', Everything looks good.

Open Sans SemiBold Regular (OpenSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'OpenSans-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Open Sans SemiBold Regular (OpenSans-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Open Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Open Sans SemiBold'.

Open Sans SemiBold Italic (OpenSans-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Open Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Open Sans SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

name

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'OpenSans-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Open Sans ExtraBold Regular (OpenSans-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Open Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Open Sans ExtraBold'.

Open Sans ExtraBold Italic (OpenSans-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Open Sans' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Open Sans ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Error

Open Sans Light Regular (OpenSans-Light.ttf)

GPOS

kern

Simple check if kern feature in GPOS table.

GPOS table does not have kerning feature. Please investigate if this meets requirements.

Warning

Open Sans Light Regular (OpenSans-Light.ttf)

kern

-/-

Check if 'kern' table in TTF font.

Font has 'kern' table. Please verify if font requires kern table or if only GPOS kerning should be in font.
For example: PowerPoint only supports a flat GPOS kerning or a kern table. So, if the customer requires PowerPoint support, a kern table is necessary.

gasp

Default

Check gasp table Default.

gasp table default is:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True
and should be:
Grid-fit = True, Do gray = True, Symmetric grid-fit = True, Symmetric smoothing = True

subtable

head

lowestRecPPEM

lowestRecPPEM is '9', but should be '9'

gasp

subtable

gasp subtable value should be one less than lowestRecPPEM (head table).

gasp subtable is '8' and should be '8'.
(head table lowestRecPPEM is '9')

Pass

Open Sans Light Regular (OpenSans-Light.ttf)

gasp

subtable

gasp subtable '8' is
'Do gray = True, Symmetric smoothing = True'
equal to MT standard
'Do gray = True, Symmetric smoothing = True'

Info

subtable

Warning

Open Sans Light Regular (OpenSans-Light.ttf)

gasp

subtable

gasp subtable is '22' but should be '8'.
(head table lowestRecPPEM is '9')

Warning

Open Sans Light Regular (OpenSans-Light.ttf)

gasp

subtable
